# Pull Request Template

When creating a pull request, use this format for the title and body.

## Title

- Short, imperative phrase (e.g. `Add Docker Compose setup`, `Fix booking overlap validation`)
- No period at the end

## Body

Use exactly these sections:

## Summary

- 1–3 bullets: what changed and why

## Test plan

- [ ] `make lint`
- [ ] `make test`
- [ ] `make build`

## Optional

- If the work closes a Linear ticket, add `Resolves ABC-123` on its own line under Summary.
- If schema or seed changed, add a bullet noting both `database/schema.sql` and `backend/scripts/seed.ts` were updated together.
- For UI changes, add manual verification under Test plan (e.g. `make dev`, book/cancel flow) and a `## Screenshots` section with before-and-after images in the PR description when possible.

## Creating the PR

```bash
gh pr create --draft --title "<title>" --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Summary

- 

## Test plan

- [ ] `make lint`
- [ ] `make test`
- [ ] `make build`

EOF
)"
```

Create a ready-for-review PR only when the user explicitly asks (omit `--draft`).
